SIMPLE: separate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Separate
<hw>Sep"a*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Separated</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Separating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>separatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>separare</ets> to separate; pfref.
<ets>se-</ets> aside + <ets>parare</ets> to make ready, prepare. See
<er>Parade</er>, and cf. <er>Sever</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
disunite; to divide; to disconnect; to sever; to part in any
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From the fine gold I <qex>separate</qex> the alloy.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Separate</qex> thyself, I pray thee, from me.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xiii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who shall <qex>separate</qex> us from the love of Christ?</q>
<rj><qau>Rom. viii. 35.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To come between; to keep apart by occupying the
space between; to lie between; <as>as, the Mediterranean Sea
<ex>separates</ex> Europe and Africa</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To set apart; to select from among others, as for a
special use or service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Separate</qex> me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I
have called thaem.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xiii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Separated flowers</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>flowers which have stamens and pistils in separate flowers;
diclinous flowers.</cd> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Separate
<hw>Sep"a*rate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To part; to become disunited;
to be disconnected; to withdraw from one another; <as>as, the family
<ex>separated</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Separate
<hw>Sep"a*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>separatus</ets>, p. p. ]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Divided from
another or others; disjoined; disconnected; separated; -- said of things
once connected.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Him that was <qex>separate</qex> from his brethren.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xlix. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unconnected; not united or associated; distinct; --
said of things that have not been connected.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For such an high priest became us, who is holy, harmless,
undefiled, <qex>separate</qex> from sinnere.</q> <rj><qau>Heb. vii.
26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Disunited from the body; disembodied; <as>as, a
<ex>separate</ex> spirit; the <ex>separate</ex> state of
souls</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Separate estate</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an estate
limited to a married woman independent of her husband.</cd> --
<col><b>Separate maintenance</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an
allowance made to a wife by her husband under deed of
separation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sep"a*rate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sep"a*rate*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separatical</ent>⟦br⟧
